Elvarian Raintree 28th Enchanter<br></font></B></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueandori.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eandori</A> at: 7/31/01 4:54:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvondu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vondu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(7/31/01 5:24:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Survey</span><hr size=1> I hated this camp but here is what my theory is:<br>
<br>
<br>
I truly believe the AC is connected to the spawns in the undead tower.  Particularly the &quot;a drybones skeleton&quot; that spawns in the tower.<br>
<br>
There are atleast 4 mobs that spawn in the tower. A &quot;crypt mummy&quot;, A &quot;ghoul&quot;, &quot;a drybone skeleton&quot;, and a rare named spawn &quot;Obetl&quot;. The tower spawn has an 8 hour EQ time spawn or an RL time of 25 minutes. In order to trigger the AC or his PH you must kill the &quot;a drybone skeleton&quot; at 8 PM EQ time. None of the other tower spawns have worked for me.<br>
<br>
Kill ALL SG's that spawn between then and 3 AM EQ time.<br>
You might want to try killing the undead too but I dont think it is necessary.<br>
At 4 AM EQ time one of the following things will happen.<br>
a) The AC will spawn in any of the possible SG spawn spots.<br>
b) The tower mob will spawn.<br>
c) Several SGs will spawn.<br>
<br>
If you dont get the AC spawn, then make sure you kill whatever is in the tower until you get another &quot;a drybone skeleton&quot;.  Then wait and kill it at 8PM EQ time, and try again.<br>
<br>
This SEEMS to be the rotation that I noticed while doing my AC camping.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usvenalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>svenalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#333333>(7/31/01 5:45:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Survey</span><hr size=1> I have gotten him in several places, and have used Scars with no resists to take him down...smack him with a malise line spell if you think you need to, but fire is the way to go in my opinion if you have Scars. Speed is of the essence when taking out the AC because he is highly contested and KS'ing is usually rampant when he appears. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzaphid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zaphid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#333333>(7/31/01 6:27:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://zaphid.50megs.com/images/headofzaphidsstaff.jpg height=60 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Survey</span><hr size=1> I have 13 jboots under my belt<br>
<br>
-AC spawns in random locations at random times (minimum hunt time was 1 minit maximum was 16 hours)<br>
-AC is free for all (you may respect first attack rules but not many others will)<br>
-Everything in the desert area is a potential place holder<br>
-AC is imune to fire use magic,cold,or poison based spells<br>
<br>
I have not seen him spawn in the same place twice. I run a circle arround the desert area killing everything in sight. Last 2 times I was there I was looking for spider silks and Terrorantula and wound up with 2 rings and gave away 2 and 1 rotted before I got the terrorantula. Hunt late at night when few people are playing is my best advice. On innoruuk it seems most people have given up on this zone. Ive been in there 5 times being the only one in the zone over the last 3 weeks.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 402<br> <font color=#333333>(7/31/01 8:28:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Survey</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Good things about the SRo AC camp</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- If you have a job and limited hours to play, you can camp the AC without waiting on a massive list (like the OOT one).<br>
<br>
- You have about the same chance as anyone else.   Rangers and Druids have a slight advantage due to track, but it all depends on where you are when it spawns.   The area is small enough that if you are standing on top of a high dune, you will likely see the AC pop before the Ranger sees it on track.<br>
<br>
- SRo AC can be taken out by a solo 34 level Mage.  Use Shock of Steel, Earth pet, and just chain cast like mad.  Being solo for this Mob is good so you won't have to roll (either that, or group with people that don't need the JBoots).  Yes, a group will improve your odds to get the AC, but not so great as to offset the odds you will have to accept in rolling for the loot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   In OOT you really need to be 49 solo, unless you are really twinked out at 44th and get some Clarity and mana reserves or something.<br>
<br>
- You can get decent loot by killing the sand giants.   SGs are a regular spawn, every 50 minutes or so.<br>
<br>
Bad things: KSers, unknown spawn point, unknown (if any) spawn trigger.<br>
<br>
If you can do the OOT, by all means do so, it is much better as you are guarenteed to get the Ring eventually, assuming you can hold the camp solo or grouped for as long as it is going to take (could be 24 hours or more, or, with luck, like 5 minutes).   That inital waiting list was what it made it impossible for me.   If you are on a PvP server, taking the camp by force might be an option -- I don't know if PvPers respect lists!<br>
<br>
In practice, the SRo camp is likely to take you longer.  The AC will pop about once or twice a day, but you are going to have to have some luck to get to it first.<br>
<br>
My first AC took me a long time (a week of effort, 3 to 5 hours a day).    The first couple days I had many guild friend popping by and grouping for a little while.  We got the AC one time, but I lost the roll on the loot (lol) to one of my best guild buddies.   I saw the AC a couple more times (the '*'s on the map), but other people got to it first.   Once time was right after a patch, I log in, and there was the AC.  So, if you see a patch scheduled, be the first into SRo right afterwards.   I took note of all these spawn points, and then just stayed real close by to them.   Sure enough, the AC pops near me, and I am the first to get to it.   A necro tried to KS it, but I already had done too much damage to it with the level 24 SoS spell chain nukes.<br>
<br>
The second time I got the AC was when I was just passing through.   Zoned in, and there he was down in the first trench.   <br>
